Robert Lopez -LRB- born February 23 , 1975 -RRB- is an American songwriter of musicals , best known for co-creating The Book of Mormon and Avenue Q , and for composing the songs featured in the Disney animated film Frozen .
He is the youngest of only twelve people who have won an Emmy , a Grammy , an Oscar , and a Tony Award , and the quickest -LRB- 10 years -RRB- to win all four .